## 🐛 Bug Report

The bug occurs when I try to do a formula like this.

<Worksheet Name>.<Range>
data.$A$2:$A$8

But when saving the file it shows on the data validation formula as cell range.

and

makes the formula like this instead.

The letter a is lowercased for example.

data.$a$2:$A$8

## Steps To Reproduce

```javascript
    const createDataValidationList = (column, start, end, sheet = "data") =>
      `${sheet}\.$${column}$${start}:$${column}$${end}`;
    console.log(categories.length);
    list.getColumn("category").eachCell(cell => {
      cell.dataValidation = {
        type: "list",
        allowBlank: true,
        formulae: [createDataValidationList("A", 2, categories.length + 1)]
      };
      console.log(cell);
    });
```

## The expected behaviour:

the formula must  be data.$A$2:$A$8
